Addressing Your Research Needs

Otis Chadley
Subjects:African American Studies, Anthropology, Family Science, Psychology, Sociology

Welcome!

This multidisciplinary guide will assist scholars conducting research in the areas of gender, family, and social change; social and economic inequality; health in social context; people and place, including population and environment, population mobility, and the impact of neighborhood and community on health and development. Click on the Research Themes tab of this guide for further explanation of the topics and recommended databases.  The Maryland Population Research Center, located on the campus of the University of Maryland at College Park will find a wealth of useful information in this online resource guide.
